popularCourses.course_desc:
This Lifetime Web Dev Membership will guide your web development journey from a novice to an expert covering front end, backend and full stack skills. This membership would provide you access to all the  existing web development courses, edegree, exams and e-books along with access to future courses and e-degrees in the domain. Learn html, css, javascript, git & github, node.js, react, angular, vue and a lot more with the lifetime membership. 

Benefits:

  • 400+ comprehensive courses for real world skill
    development.
  • 2000+ hours of web development training.
  • 20000+ video lectures from world-class instructors.
  • 50+ Technologies
  • Latest and most popular web technologies covered.
  • 100+ hours of latest Web Dev content added every month.

This Massive 40+ hour course covers all the different segments that a
developer must learn and seamlessly stitches them together to give the learner a wholesome experience. The developer will go through the entire five segments step by step, learning how to see the puzzle as a big picture rather than in pieces.
Our Full Stack Course breaks down the fundamentals of each technology that you would require to become a Full Stack Developer. The entire course is broken down into five separate segments: Frontend, Backend, Database, Other Essential Technologies, and Debugging/Version Control. Each section includes multiple technologies to help you gain more experience as a developer.

Benefits:-

  •  Frontend - HTML, HMTL5, CSS3, Twitter Bootstrap, JavaScript, jQuery
  • Backend - Node.js, Meteor.js, Angular 2, PHP, Ruby on Rails
  • Database - MySQL, PostgreSQL, Mongo DB, Couch DB, Apache Cassandra
  • Debugging/Version Control - GIT, Subversion, Task Runners (Grunt, Gulp), Debuggers

popularCourses.course_title: Certificate Program in Strategic Management and Business Essentials
popularCourses.course_desc:
Hero Vired and INSEAD have collaboratively designed a program on Strategic Management and Business Essentials to provide you with the tools and techniques to become a more effective leader.

This program integrates various business concepts from marketing to operations to sales and finance. In addition, the program not only equips you with theoretical knowledge of core business functions but provides application-based learning through workshops, business simulations, and case studies to help enhance your leadership skills.

This program will cater to mid-senior professionals, entrepreneurs, and senior leaders looking to take their leadership skills to the next level.

On successful completion of this Strategic Management program, learners will be eligible for a Hero Vired and INSEAD Certificate.

popularCourses.course_title: Certificate Program in Financial Analysis, Valuation & Risk Management
popularCourses.course_desc:
The Certificate Program in Financial Analysis, Valuation & Risk Management aims to offer the participants the comprehensive instructions and training required to compete successfully in swiftly developing financial markets. In addition, you will learn to evaluate the financial consequences of business decisions and how to value companies, businesses, and investments.

The program focuses on the core areas of finance with a theoretical grounding in fundamental concepts of time value, bond mathematics, portfolio theory, financial statements, and accounting.

On successful completion of this program, learners will receive a Hero Vired and a Columbia University’s (Columbia X) Professional Certificate

popularCourses.course_title: Certificate Program in FinTech, Blockchain, & Cryptocurrencies
popularCourses.course_desc:
The program will help you explore the fundamentals of FinTech. It covers the emerging technologies of blockchain, cryptocurrency, and metaverse technologies and will help develop problem-solving skills.

The program is designed for anyone looking to explore and evaluate the transformational technologies that are changing the world of investment & finance. It benefits people working on blockchain technology or managerial roles in financial institutions.

On successful completion of this program, learners will receive a Certificate from Hero Vired.

jobsArticles.author: Via IANS

jobsArticles.title: Tech layoffs shock young workers, but not older ones
jobsArticles.shortDescription: Tech’s generational divide is representative of a broader phenomenon. The year someone is born has a big influence on views about work and money. Early personal experiences strongly determine a person’s appetite for financial risk, according to a 2011 study by economists Ulrike Malmendier of the University of California, Berkeley and Stefan Nagel of the University of Chicago.
jobsArticles.author: Via New York Times

jobsArticles.title: IT staff’s pay hike hopes down 40 percent in December as job market cools
jobsArticles.shortDescription: Attrition has tapered from peak levels of 25-30% last year to about 20% in the December quarter and the consequent lag in salary hikes is likely to help companies improve operating margins, which have been under pressure due to the high cost of talent.
jobsArticles.author: By Romita Majumdar & Sai Ishwarbharath

jobsArticles.title: Tier 2 markets see increasing participation from female workers
jobsArticles.shortDescription: In 2022, jobs and professional networking platform 'apna' witnessed more than 31 million professional conversations among women from tier 1, tier 2, and beyond cities with an overall 36 per cent year-on-year increase in women users on the platform. As per the report, apna saw around 80 per cent increase in the number of new women users on its platform.
jobsArticles.author: Via PTI

jobsArticles.title: Campus blues: mass layoffs put IITians on edge
jobsArticles.shortDescription: Microsoft, Amazon, Google and Goldman Sachs have operations in India and also are regular recruiters at top Indian campuses including IITs. This year, both Microsoft and Amazon are hiring fewer numbers from the campuses, according to multiple placement sources
jobsArticles.author: By Prachi Verma & Sreeradha Basu

jobsArticles.title: About 3,000 tech employees now being fired a day on average in Jan
jobsArticles.shortDescription: In 2022, over 1,000 companies laid off 154,336 workers, as per the data by layoffs tracking site Layoffs.fyi. The mass tech layoffs of 2022 are continuing into the new year, and Indian companies and startups are also among the leaders in firing staff.
jobsArticles.author: Via IANS

jobsArticles.title: Mining workers approach SC over hiring of retrenched staff
jobsArticles.shortDescription: "Till such time as the new mine operators commence operation, it is necessary that the Goa government be directed to pay the workmen a subsistence allowance not less than the minimum wages fixed by the government for digging, excavation and mining operations," stated the union in the petition.
jobsArticles.author: Via TNN

jobsArticles.title: Swiggy to lay off 380 Employees, says CEO
jobsArticles.shortDescription: The food and grocery delivery company is the latest to join the swelling ranks of startups such as ShareChat, Dunzo, Rebel Foods, Hubilo, Ola and Cashfree to announce layoffs in recent weeks, as the sector weathers a late –stage funding crunch amid global macro-economic and geopolitical turmoil.
jobsArticles.author: Via ETtech

jobsArticles.title: Cooler hiring and milder pay gains could aid inflation fight
jobsArticles.shortDescription: With companies continuing to add jobs across the economy, the unemployment rate fell from 3.6% to 3.5%, matching a 53-year low, the Labor Department said Friday.
jobsArticles.author: By Josh Boak | Associated Press Writer

jobsArticles.title: Why Are There Job Cuts at the Top IT Companies?
jobsArticles.shortDescription: In many ways, this significant round of lay-offs is a correction for an earlier error. Our internet lives have primarily replaced our offline lives over the epidemic years.
jobsArticles.author: By Raghav Agrawal | Times Ascent

jobsArticles.title: Companies to Increase Campus Hiring
jobsArticles.shortDescription: The recruitment of new talent, which is less expensive and easier to keep than lateral entry, is increasing dramatically among IT majors. Although the numbers are growing, the average entry-level compensation has remained constant, except for several institutes that reported high offers.
jobsArticles.author: By Raghav Agrawal | Times Ascent

jobsArticles.title: Is Going Back to Work Expensive?
jobsArticles.shortDescription: Companies want us back at our desks, which is not surprising. Businesses of all sizes and sorts would only suffer financial losses with regular trips and meals. There is a problem, however. Employees who have not budgeted for lunches, train tickets, or new office attire for the past two years know how much it costs to sit at a desk all day.
jobsArticles.author: By Raghav Agrawal | Times Ascent

jobsArticles.title: Use of unregistered devices by employees increasing risks around hybrid work, says survey
jobsArticles.shortDescription: With hybrid model empowering employees to work remotely and ensuring business continuity for enterprises, the use of unregistered devices by employees to access work platforms is adding new security challenges for organisations in India, according to a new survey by Cisco.
jobsArticles.author: Via PTI

jobsArticles.title: Quiet Quitting: A wakeup call for companies? Here's what HRs can do about it!
jobsArticles.shortDescription: Quiet Quitting actually gained relevance in China in 2021 when an Internet user criticised companies for making workers prioritise their work over mental wellbeing.
jobsArticles.author: By Tejaswini Singhal

jobsArticles.title: Non-IT sectors continue to drive white collar jobs in December
jobsArticles.shortDescription: Hiring activity in December ended 4% higher compared to the same month a year ago despite global macroeconomic headwinds. The momentum generated in the beginning of 2022 sustained into the second half of this year, barring a few key sectors.
jobsArticles.author: By Rica Bhattacharyya

jobsArticles.title: Salesforce layoffs impact India employees too
jobsArticles.shortDescription: A Chennai-based associate technical support engineer at Salesforce, Romario Xavier, in a Linked/n note said, "I never thought my career with Salesforce would end soon. Laid off from Salesforce and looking for an opportunity as Salesforce administrator. Any support would be appreciated." He had joined Salesforce in October.
jobsArticles.author: By Shilpa Phadnis

jobsArticles.title: India has its work cut out in terms of jobs
jobsArticles.shortDescription: The jobless growth phenomenon in India predates Covid, but the urgency of addressing it has become sharper in the shadow of the pandemic.
jobsArticles.author: By Ashwini Deshpande

jobsArticles.title: Blue-collar jobs scene looking bright
jobsArticles.shortDescription: According to the data, the number of job vacancies in the blue and grey collar industry increased by 301% in the past year to 10,542,820 in 2022 from 2,626,637 in 2021. The number of job seekers in the blue and grey collar industry have also grown by 236%.
jobsArticles.author: By Rica Bhattacharyya

jobsArticles.title: Bank staff to strike work on Jan 30 & 31
jobsArticles.shortDescription: "UFBU meeting was held today in Mumbai. since there is no response from Indian Banks' Association (IBA) on our demands despite letters, it has been decided to revive our agitation and to give a call for strike on January 30 and 31," AIBEA General Secretary C.H. Venkatachalam told IANS.
jobsArticles.author: Via IANS

jobsArticles.title: India Inc likely to get cautious in hiring during January-March quarter
jobsArticles.shortDescription: About 48% of Indian employers covered in the latest ManpowerGroup Employment Outlook Survey, shared exclusively with ET, said they will hire more people in the March quarter, 16% expect a decrease in hiring intent and 34% expected to keep workforce levels steady. Only 2% were unsure about hiring intentions.
jobsArticles.author: By Sreeradha Basu

jobsArticles.title: Getting future-ready: Here's how to prepare today for tomorrow’s jobs
jobsArticles.shortDescription: An additional degree or a specialist course can build on your current skills to boost your job role or position you as a knowledge leader in your existing industry.
jobsArticles.author: By Professor Heather McGregor, Provost and Vice Principal of Heriot-Watt University Dubai

Asia Edge Pte Ltd (PetroEdge & PowerEdge) are proud recipients of the Enterprise 50 (E50) Award.

Established in 1995, the E50 Award is a valuable endorsement and highly coveted mark of recognition that highlights the significant efforts of the 50 most enterprising local, privately-held companies who have contributed to the economic development of Singapore. It is jointly organised by The Business Times and KPMG in Singapore, with support from Enterprise Singapore, the Singapore Business Federation and the Singapore Exchange.

PetroEdge is the leading Oil & Gas training specialist in the Asia Pacific region. Since inception in 2007, we have provided targeted and in-depth training courses to develop the competency and capabilities of engineers, geoscientists, technicians and related professionals in leading National & International Oil Companies across the region. We deliver our learning content through webinars, e-learning and face to face classroom teaching. We annually execute over 300 courses and cover various disciplines from engineering, science, strategy to management.

The Role

Your Responsibilities will include: 

Human Resource—

  • Drafting and placing of job advertisements on job portals locally and internationally
  • Responsible for recruitment of local and international staff and co-ordination of interviews;
  • Prepare employment contract and company handbook
  • Manage staff on-boarding and exit processes
  • Apply and process work passes
  • Custodian for employee personal files
  • Coordinate with E2i and SNEF for related courses and grants
  • Oversee employee welfare and benefits
  • Other HR-related matters

Administration—

  • Manage company's insurance and membership renewal;
  • Oversee office maintenance, relocation, and renovation including sourcing and liaising with suppliers and contractors;
  • Estate management such as liaising with landlord, tenants, building management and property agents;
  • Managing staff attendance reports; and
  • Ad-hoc administrative requirements

Ideal Profile

Skills Required: 

  • Minimum Diploma holder with a minimum of 5 years of working experience in office administration and HR
  • Independent and willing to take challenges
  • Meticulous with strong attention to details
  • Able to commence within short notice
  • Position available for Singaporean and PR Holders only
  • You are organised and have good interpersonal skills.
  • You have good computer skills (MS Word, Excel, PowerPoint).
  • You can work with minimal supervision and multi-task effectively.
  • You pay strong attention to detail and deliver work that is of a high standard
  • You are a strong team player who can manage multiple stakeholders
  • You are adaptable and thrive in changing environments

What's on Offer?

  • Role involving team management opportunities
  • Great work culture
  • Opportunities for career growth & development
  • Birthday paid leave
  • Outpatient medical benefits
  • Company hospitalization plan

We at Corporate Resources with over eighteen years (18yrs as of 2022) of experience in Human Resource Management and Consulting help you find the right candidates for your company, partner with you in maximizing the potential of your human capital and optimize your HR processes.

The Role

Your Responsibilities will include: 

  • Writing well-designed, testable and efficient code.
  • Gathering and evaluating user feedback.
  • Working as a part of a dynamic team to deliver winning products.
  • Providing code documentation and other inputs to technical documents.
  • Supporting continuous improvement by investigating alternatives and new technologies and presenting these for architectural review.
  • Troubleshooting and debugging to optimise performance.
  • Analysing business requirements to develop technical network solutions and their framework.
  • Providing technical (Level 2/Level 3) support.
  • Providing design guidelines, documentation, standard configuration and best practices for implementation.
  • Understanding available solutions and be aware of best practices within the industry.
  • Working closely with stakeholders to understand requirements.

Ideal Profile

Skills Required: 

  • You possess a Degree/Diploma in Computer Science, Engineering or related field.
  • You have solid years of experience, ideally within a Software Engineer, IT Business Analyst / Project Manager or Network Architect role.
  • You have good interpersonal and communication skills and are adept at working with multiple stakeholders to drive desired outcomes.
  • Good knowledge of MySQL, NOSQL (MongoDB, Cassandra, Elasticsearch, Hbase, DynamoDB) and Ingres databases.
  • You are highly goal driven and work well in fast paced environments
  • You possess strong analytical skills and are comfortable dealing with numerical data
  • You are a strong mentor and coach who can build high performing teams

What's on Offer?

  • Work within a company with a solid track record of success
  • Join a well known brand within IT Software
  • Great work environment
